# Feature Components

## Component Structure

- Keep business logic in hooks/utils (not in components)
- Use TypeScript for all component props
- Handle loading and error states appropriately
- Keep components focused and small (< 200 lines ideally)
- Prefer composition over prop drilling

## Props & Types

- Define proper TypeScript interfaces for props
- Use discriminated unions for variant props
- Avoid optional props when possible - be explicit
- Document complex props with JSDoc comments

## State Management

- Keep state as local as possible
- Use Zustand for global client state (when needed)
- Prefer React Query for server state
- Use React Context for theme, auth, and cross-cutting concerns
- Avoid prop drilling - use context or state management when appropriate

## React Best Practices

- Use functional components exclusively
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Follow rules of hooks
- Use React.memo() judiciously (only when proven necessary)
- Implement proper error boundaries

## Styling (Tailwind CSS)

- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use `@altitutor/ui` components from shared package when available
- Leverage `clsx` or `cn()` utility for conditional classes
- Use Radix UI primitives for accessible components

## Display Utilities

- **Always use formatter utilities for consistent display:**
  - Classes: `formatClassName()` or `formatClassShortName()`
  - Subjects: `formatSubjectDisplay()` or `formatSubjectShortName()`
  - Import from `shared/utils`
- **Always use enum color utilities for badges and status displays:**
  - Import color helpers from `shared/utils/enum-colors` or `@altitutor/ui`
  - Use functions like `getStudentStatusColor()`, `getSubjectCurriculumColor()`, etc.
  - Never hardcode badge colors - use the centralized color mappings

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Add proper ARIA labels where needed
- Test with screen readers
- Maintain color contrast ratios (WCAG AA minimum)

## Performance

- Implement virtualization for long lists (react-virtual)
- Optimize images using Next.js Image component
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting when appropriate
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
